---
import BlogPost from '@/layouts/BlogPost.astro';

const title = "Airbnb During Chinese New Year: Pricing and Preparation Guide";
const description = "Complete guide to preparing your Melaka Airbnb for Chinese New Year 2026. Pricing strategies, preparation checklist, guest management, and maximizing revenue during peak festival season.";
const date = "2026-01-30";
const category = "educational";
const language = "en";
const image = "/images/blog/airbnb-cny-pricing-guide.jpg";

const content = `
<h1>Airbnb During Chinese New Year: Pricing and Preparation Guide</h1>

<p>Chinese New Year 2026 (January 29 - February 12) is <strong>the most profitable period</strong> for Melaka Airbnbs. Proper preparation and pricing can generate <strong>25-35% of annual revenue</strong> in just 15 days.</p>

<h2>CNY 2026 Calendar</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>CNY Eve:</strong> January 29, 2026</li>
<li><strong>15-day festival:</strong> January 29 - February 12, 2026</li>
<li><strong>Peak demand:</strong> January 29 - February 7 (Days 1-10)</li>
<li><strong>Shoulder demand:</strong> February 8-12 (Days 11-15)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Optimal Pricing Strategy</h2>

<p><strong>Tiered pricing structure:</strong></p>

<table class="w-full">
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>CNY Period</th>
<th><strong>Pricing Action</th>
<th><strong>Rate Increase</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Pre-CNY (Jan 1-28)</td>
>List for CNY, secure early bookings</td>
<td>+30-40%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>CNY Peak (Jan 29 - Feb 7)</strong></td>
<td>Maximize rates, enforce minimum stays</td>
<td><strong>+50-60%</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Late CNY (Feb 8-12)</td>
<td>Maintain premium, fill remaining gaps</td>
<td>+20-30%</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Minimum stays by period:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>CNY Eve - Day 3: 4-5 night minimum</li>
<li>Day 4-9: 3-4 night minimum</li>
<li>Day 10+: 2-3 night minimum</li>
</ul>

<h2>Preparation Checklist (Do in December)</h2>

<p><strong>30 days before CNY:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Professional photography with CNY decorations</li>
<li>Update listings with CNY-themed descriptions</li>
<li>Stock extra supplies (linens, toiletries, essentials)</li>
<li>Preventative maintenance inspection</li>
<li>Contact service providers about holiday schedule</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>7 days before CNY:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Install CNY decorations (lanterns, couplets, flowers)</li>
<li>Prepare welcome baskets with CNY treats</li>
<li>Test all appliances and systems</li>
<li>Confirm all booking details with guests</li>
</ul>

<h2>Guest Communication Strategy</h2>

<p><strong>Pre-arrival messaging:</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>CNY event highlights happening during stay</li>
attractions within walking distance
Local CNY food recommendations
Emergency contact information
CNY-specific house rules (if any)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>During stay:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Proactive communication about local events</li>
<li>Responsive issue resolution (under 15 minutes)</li>
<li>Local recommendations for CNY activities</li>
</ul>

<h2>Maximizing CNY Revenue</h2>

<p><strong>Revenue optimization tips:</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>List early (September for CNY)</li>
<li>Accept longer minimum stays for premium rates</li>
<li>Offer add-on experiences (heritage tours, food crawls)</li>
<li>Maintain competitive pricing (monitor rates daily)</li>
<li>Use 5-platform listing for maximum exposure</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Target guests:</strong> Families (40%), Singaporean weekenders (25%), cultural tourists (20%), couples (15%).</p>

<h2>Post-CNY Strategy</h2>

<p><strong>Extend the season:</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Offer late-leaver discounts for guests extending into February</li>
<li>Request reviews mentioning "CNY experience"</li>
<li>Add CNY photos to listing for future marketing</li>
<li>Plan for Chap Goh Meh (Feb 12) promotions</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>WhatsApp +60166996688</strong> for complete CNY preparation and pricing strategy.</p>
`;
